# {{context|statistics}} A [[probability distribution]] such that for a [[random variable]] ''X'' with that distribution holds that the probability that ''X'' is greater than some number ''x'' is given by<br><math>\Pr(X>x)=\left(\frac{x}{x_\mathrm{m}}\right)^{-k}</math><br>for all ''x'' ≥ ''x''<sub>m</sub>, where ''x''<sub>m</sub> is the (necessarily positive) minimum possible value of ''X'', and ''k'' is a positive parameter.

